                    <span>The concepts and ideas presented in this book (as well as the Business Objects book) should be in the "toolbox" of every serious Visual Basic developer. The examples are concise and the concepts are easy to read and understand. I recently developed an n-tier e-commerce web application using the author's concepts for the middle tier. This was my first full-scale, enterprise-level effort, and I found the architecture easy to implement and the performance and scalability to be superb.<P>Incidentally, the support from the author and publisher are excellent as well. When I had a question about the subject matter in the book, I e-mailed the author. I received a personal reply from Mr. Lhotka, with a detailed answer to my question, in just a couple of days.</span>
                  
